WEBVTT

00:03.086 --> 00:05.714
I found Strauss' go-between,
a paralegal named Juliana Barnes.

00:05.881 --> 00:08.634
- Tell me about Daisy and Kyle.
- They were Strauss' students.

00:08.800 --> 00:11.053
MARK:
I have to initiate all bodily contact.

00:11.595 --> 00:13.438
Why pretend to help me avenge my family?

00:13.597 --> 00:16.315
Because Andrew said
that you were the perfect patsy.

00:16.517 --> 00:18.485
Get on your knees.

00:18.894 --> 00:21.067
MAN: Experts say
he couldn't have survived that fall.

00:21.230 --> 00:23.153
Well, he's a cockroach, he survived.

00:27.110 --> 00:30.535
Got a hit on one of the employees
at Manitech Securities named Sam Lewis.

00:30.697 --> 00:32.290
His real name is Theo Noble.

00:32.448 --> 00:34.952
- Why are you doing this?
THEO: Because they found me.

00:37.496 --> 00:39.715
You had a beautiful family.
Why not just leave?

00:39.873 --> 00:43.377
- Because I control their fate, not you.
- I am gonna end you.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.091
THEO:
Be careful, Agent Hardy.

00:45.254 --> 00:49.304
I am the man who will take your future,
piece by piece.

00:49.466 --> 00:52.845
- Joe Carroll is the worst form of cancer.
- So his death is about revenge.

00:53.011 --> 00:57.016
His death is about justice. If you can't
understand that, you should get the hell out.

00:57.182 --> 01:00.903
- I was clear that I needed this to go well.
- Me and Joe were almost blown up!

01:01.061 --> 01:02.563
You are really losing it, Ryan.

01:46.064 --> 01:47.407
Shh.

02:07.794 --> 02:09.512
So how do we do this?

02:09.670 --> 02:12.390
I have so much to teach you.

02:19.181 --> 02:20.398
[GASPS]

02:20.557 --> 02:23.481
MAN [ON TV]:
...for Joe Carroll's reign of terror...

02:23.644 --> 02:25.521
...had come to an end.
- Hi. You okay?

02:25.687 --> 02:29.408
Oh, yeah. No, I'm good, I'm good.
It's just a bad, bad dream.

02:30.859 --> 02:33.863
Joe Carroll.
No wonder you were having nightmares.

02:35.113 --> 02:37.582
It must've come on when I was asleep.

02:38.116 --> 02:40.118
You shouldn't be sleeping out here.

02:40.285 --> 02:42.128
This isn't us.

02:42.287 --> 02:44.130
I don't wanna fight anymore.

02:44.289 --> 02:46.007
Me either.

02:46.458 --> 02:52.056
MAN: And uncover the truth behind Arthur
Strauss, the man who mentored Carroll.

02:52.214 --> 02:55.639
How many more
of his psychotic students...

02:55.801 --> 02:57.303
[MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

02:57.469 --> 02:59.096
Come to bed.

02:59.262 --> 03:04.268
MAN: Brave the cold, dark night
and return to the scene of the crime...

03:04.643 --> 03:09.240
...as we count down
to The Execution of Joe Carroll.

05:11.353 --> 05:12.775
Stay there.

05:13.772 --> 05:16.150
[GASPING AND GURGLING]

05:29.538 --> 05:31.791
I know this is a pain.

05:32.457 --> 05:37.258
Hey, I'm the only ER doctor in New York
with an armed escort to work.

05:37.420 --> 05:40.173
And the gym and the dry cleaner. Heh.

05:40.340 --> 05:41.512
Yeah, it sucks, I get it.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.894
But these threats are real.

05:44.761 --> 05:46.763
So this is our new normal.

05:46.930 --> 05:50.230
No, we get our lives back
as soon as I find him.

05:50.392 --> 05:51.439
Believe me...

05:52.310 --> 05:53.857
...I'll find him.

05:54.187 --> 05:55.609
I know you will.

05:56.857 --> 05:57.949
[SIREN WAILING]

05:58.108 --> 06:00.657
COP [OVER SPEAKER]:
Driver, pull over to the side of the road.

06:00.819 --> 06:01.991
What the hell?

06:11.621 --> 06:15.046
- Hands! Let me see your hands!
- Officer, what's going on?

06:15.208 --> 06:18.052
- Out. Hands where we can see them.
- Let's go.

06:18.336 --> 06:20.634
RYAN: Okay, okay.
GWEN: Ryan.

06:20.797 --> 06:22.470
COP 1: Slowly.
COP 2: Let's go, move.

06:23.466 --> 06:24.638
Gun, gun, gun!

06:26.595 --> 06:28.973
All right. Whoa, whoa, whoa. I'm FBI.

06:29.139 --> 06:31.813
I got a shield, left coat pocket.

06:41.610 --> 06:44.159
Agent Hardy, I didn't recognize you.

06:44.321 --> 06:45.823
- This is your car?
- Yeah.

06:46.281 --> 06:48.283
COP 1:
I'm very sorry. I don't know what happened.

06:48.450 --> 06:50.498
Sometimes our computer
has a mind of its own.

06:51.161 --> 06:53.459
- Your computer?
- Yeah, your car came up stolen.

06:53.830 --> 06:57.551
A suspect fitting your description
was described as armed and dangerous.

06:58.168 --> 07:00.921
COP 1: I'm sorry, agent.
COP 2: We're very sorry, sir.

07:01.087 --> 07:02.430
Ma'am.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.310
What the hell was that all about?

07:24.819 --> 07:26.492
[IN ARABIC]

07:33.870 --> 07:35.497
[IN ENGLISH]
You look weary, sir.

07:35.664 --> 07:37.883
It was a difficult shoot.
I'm thankful to be home.

07:38.041 --> 07:40.669
- It's good to have you back.
- Thank you.

07:41.169 --> 07:42.637
Where's... Where's Penny?

07:43.004 --> 07:44.972
She's been gone several days.

07:47.133 --> 07:50.387
- I see.
- I'll let you settle in, sir. I'll return tomorrow?

07:51.012 --> 07:52.309
[IN ARABIC]

08:22.377 --> 08:24.004
- Hey, man.
- Hey.

08:32.721 --> 08:34.849
- I'll see you out there.
- Yeah.

08:40.602 --> 08:45.279
Hey. So I did what you asked. I went through
the evidence from Mark's safe house.

08:45.442 --> 08:47.615
- Top to bottom.
- Gonna tell me I'm crazy, right?

08:47.777 --> 08:49.825
- I'm chasing ghosts.
- I might have something.

08:50.196 --> 08:53.951
- Evidence that a computer was in use.
- There was no computer in the evidence log.

08:54.117 --> 08:58.338
But there was an open Ethernet line
with an unusually high data-transfer rate.

08:58.747 --> 09:02.001
Someone in that house
was spending a lot of time online.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.670
Missing computer, this is good.
So how do we find it?

09:04.836 --> 09:07.009
SLOAN: We have to isolate its BIA,
burned-in address.

09:07.172 --> 09:09.675
Once we have that, it'll gate us to an IP.

09:09.841 --> 09:11.263
And to Mark.

09:14.137 --> 09:15.810
Guys.

09:15.972 --> 09:17.815
- Status report. Conference room.
- Okay.

09:17.974 --> 09:19.647
Thank you.

09:23.480 --> 09:26.529
So you're telling me Theo Noble
didn't exist before 2007.

09:26.691 --> 09:29.991
It was a cover like the Sam Lewis ID he
used when he worked at Manitech Securities.

09:30.153 --> 09:31.245
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

09:31.404 --> 09:33.998
So he creates these identities why?

09:34.157 --> 09:35.204
Primarily to kill.

09:35.408 --> 09:39.208
Although Sam Lewis did give him
crucial access to the FBI servers.

09:39.412 --> 09:41.835
There's no way of knowing
how many identities he has.

09:41.998 --> 09:44.842
But with Theo Noble,
he had the perfect cover life.

09:45.001 --> 09:49.552
And I think he saw his family as sacrosanct,
which is why he never killed in that identity.

09:50.173 --> 09:54.349
And when we forced him to destroy
his family, we took away his safety net.

09:54.511 --> 09:55.854
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

09:57.430 --> 10:00.274
- What else?
- We've been running on the theory...

10:00.433 --> 10:04.438
...that he hides his serial killing
in murder-suicides.

10:04.604 --> 10:07.733
So we isolated 30 cases
that fit the profile.

10:07.899 --> 10:09.651
No indication of suicidal tendencies.

10:09.859 --> 10:11.782
The death scenes could have been staged.

10:11.945 --> 10:14.994
And in each case,
there's a history of chatroom usage.

10:15.156 --> 10:17.079
Thirty could be just the beginning.

10:17.242 --> 10:18.414
We need a nationwide search.

10:18.576 --> 10:19.623
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

10:19.786 --> 10:20.833
Just answer it.

10:24.249 --> 10:25.967
Ryan Hardy.

10:26.459 --> 10:28.757
What? Used to buy what?

10:28.920 --> 10:32.470
No. Listen, I gotta call you back.

10:35.009 --> 10:36.977
That was fraud alert.

10:37.137 --> 10:40.437
My credit card was used
to buy a motorboat in Utah.

10:40.598 --> 10:44.023
And my car came up as stolen today
on the N.Y.P.D. database.

10:44.477 --> 10:47.777
Theo hacked your personal info.
He's hitting you where you live.

10:47.939 --> 10:51.489
- He's trying to knock you off-balance.
- Call just came in from N.Y.P.D.

10:51.651 --> 10:54.495
A break-in and murder
at Juliana Barnes' law office.

10:54.654 --> 10:55.826
Juliana Barnes?

10:55.989 --> 10:58.037
Didn't we seize everything
after her murder?

11:00.660 --> 11:04.460
Okay. All right, we got locals
on the scene. One victim.

11:04.622 --> 11:07.171
A security guard, his throat was slashed.

11:07.333 --> 11:11.213
It doesn't make sense.
Why hit the office of Strauss' paralegal?

11:12.505 --> 11:15.054
There's gotta be something hidden there
that we missed.

11:17.177 --> 11:20.477
- You all right? Everybody okay? You okay?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm okay.

11:26.477 --> 11:27.569
Is she okay?

11:29.147 --> 11:31.195
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

11:32.525 --> 11:35.449
- Hello.
THEO: That looked like it hurt.

11:37.197 --> 11:39.541
- Where are you?
- Everywhere.

11:40.033 --> 11:44.209
I'm in your traffic lights,
your credit report, your e-mail account.

11:44.370 --> 11:46.543
This just came up. From Jenny.

11:46.956 --> 11:48.208
"Miss you, big bro."

11:48.541 --> 11:49.838
Smiley face.

11:50.001 --> 11:53.676
- You keep my sister out of this.
- You can't count the ways I can get to you.

11:53.838 --> 11:55.055
Hey, guess what, Theo.

11:55.215 --> 11:56.967
You're just one man.

11:57.717 --> 12:02.769
I got a thousand FBI agents on my side,
and I will take those odds any day.

12:02.972 --> 12:07.443
All the agents in the world
won't be able to save you.

12:07.602 --> 12:11.527
You need to be punished for what you did
to me, and I'm just getting started.

12:29.207 --> 12:31.426
- You think this was Theo?
RYAN: Let's think about it.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.757
Juliana was Strauss' go-between.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.799
She's the one that reached out
to Kyle and Daisy and Andrew.

12:37.006 --> 12:41.307
Strauss gave her their contact information.
He could've given her something on Theo.

12:41.469 --> 12:43.517
What if he gave her info on other students?

12:43.680 --> 12:45.978
Joe said that Strauss
kept his students separate.

12:46.140 --> 12:48.689
They had no way of contacting one another.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.312
Maybe that's what Theo wants...

12:51.479 --> 12:54.653
...to contact Strauss' other students.

12:56.317 --> 12:57.364
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

13:16.838 --> 13:18.340
[GUNSHOT]

13:20.383 --> 13:21.555
THEO:
Nice shooting.

13:23.052 --> 13:25.851
- You military?
- I was.

13:26.180 --> 13:27.557
Twelfth Mountain, Fort Lee.

13:28.016 --> 13:29.689
THEO:
What happened?

13:29.851 --> 13:30.898
It's a long story.

13:31.519 --> 13:33.692
- I know what that's like.
- You Army too?

13:33.855 --> 13:35.072
Yeah, 28th Infantry.

13:35.940 --> 13:37.863
Harrisburg.

13:38.026 --> 13:40.404
My CO ran me out of basic, week nine.

13:45.908 --> 13:50.379
Worst part, guys like that,
they get away with it, you know.

13:51.247 --> 13:52.874
Guys like us...

13:54.500 --> 13:55.547
...we get nothing.

13:55.960 --> 13:57.633
Hell, yeah.

14:00.882 --> 14:02.054
[GUNSHOT]

14:02.216 --> 14:04.264
Oh. That's a center shot.

14:04.427 --> 14:05.724
[CHUCKLES]

14:05.887 --> 14:07.104
You got skills, man.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.731
[CHUCKLES]

14:08.890 --> 14:10.733
We should grab a beer.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.568
Sure.

14:12.727 --> 14:14.104
Shoot for a buzz?

14:15.355 --> 14:16.402
You're on.

14:24.113 --> 14:25.786
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

14:25.948 --> 14:27.575
[CHATTERING]

14:44.759 --> 14:45.976
Hey, handsome.

14:47.470 --> 14:49.472
- What can I do you for?
- Another vodka over.

14:49.639 --> 14:50.936
You got it, sugar.

14:52.100 --> 14:54.194
You sure that's all you want?

14:54.602 --> 14:58.448
How come you aren't dancing? You're
prettier than every girl in this place.

14:58.606 --> 15:00.779
Heh. You're sweet.

15:00.942 --> 15:03.491
I'm shy. All these eyes on me
would make me nervous.

15:03.653 --> 15:05.951
How about just two eyes?

15:06.781 --> 15:10.331
I got a beach house 10 minutes from here.

15:10.493 --> 15:11.745
How about you come by tonight?

15:11.911 --> 15:13.163
[CHUCKLES]

15:14.831 --> 15:16.458
Well, I do love the ocean.

15:36.811 --> 15:39.860
As your court-appointed attorney,
I am obligated to provide you...

15:40.022 --> 15:42.821
...a full briefing of your final day
prior to execution.

15:42.984 --> 15:45.988
And are you aware of how things, uh...

15:46.320 --> 15:49.870
...terminated with my previous counsel?

15:51.325 --> 15:54.545
I'm well aware of all your murders,
Mr. Carroll.

15:54.704 --> 15:59.175
So let's be clear. I don't wanna be here. If
you don't mind, I'm just gonna do my job.

15:59.375 --> 16:01.343
Yeah, by all means.

16:01.502 --> 16:04.381
Your last 24 hours will begin
with a full physical.

16:05.006 --> 16:08.010
You have your choice of a final meal.

16:08.176 --> 16:12.181
- Religious counseling will be made available.
- Ha, ha. Hmm.

16:13.222 --> 16:17.693
If you so desire. Time has been set aside
for personal visitation.

16:18.186 --> 16:22.032
Once the execution has been carried out,
you have a choice of...

16:22.190 --> 16:25.364
STUDENT: Poe's such a tragic figure.
- Yes, he was.

16:25.526 --> 16:29.372
Death was a motif in his life
just as much as his work.

16:29.530 --> 16:32.033
His parents both died
when he was very young.

16:32.200 --> 16:34.248
A brother, a sister, a wife.

16:34.410 --> 16:35.878
- Uh, Professor Carroll.
- Yes?

16:36.037 --> 16:39.382
You mentioned in your lecture
that Poe committed his life to writing...

16:39.540 --> 16:41.087
...after his brother's death?

16:41.250 --> 16:43.753
Yes, that was his chief inspiration.

16:43.920 --> 16:45.888
Was it his guilt that drove him?

16:46.047 --> 16:47.720
Did he feel responsible?

16:47.882 --> 16:49.008
[CHUCKLES]

16:49.175 --> 16:52.349
Are you suggesting that Poe
murdered his own brother?

16:52.512 --> 16:53.559
[CARROLL CHUCKLES]

16:53.721 --> 16:58.272
No evidence exists for that, and certainly,
that's the first time I've heard that accusation.

16:58.434 --> 17:00.903
Maybe it's because Poe was smart.

17:01.562 --> 17:02.905
He stayed under the water...

17:03.898 --> 17:05.650
...and never aroused suspicion.

17:05.816 --> 17:07.409
Isn't that possible?

17:08.319 --> 17:11.071
I'm sorry, I didn't quite catch your name.

17:11.239 --> 17:12.912
I gotta get to class.

17:13.741 --> 17:16.744
STUDENT:
Poe had a unique take on death, didn't he?

17:17.161 --> 17:18.913
Professor?

17:19.079 --> 17:23.256
Sorry. Yes, yes. Unique, absolutely.

17:25.920 --> 17:27.137
Any final requests?

17:29.257 --> 17:33.103
Yes, I do have one, actually.
I'd like to send a message to Ryan Hardy.

17:33.803 --> 17:38.559
Tell him I have some information
about the man he's looking for.

17:43.646 --> 17:46.024
Hey. What's wrong?
What are you doing here?

17:46.190 --> 17:49.285
Ryan, it's insane. I've been brought
under review at the hospital.

17:49.652 --> 17:50.699
For what?

17:50.861 --> 17:53.785
My electronic medication record
shows a discrepancy.

17:53.948 --> 17:56.326
It says I'm overprescribing meds,
but it's a lie.

17:56.951 --> 17:58.123
It's Theo.

17:58.286 --> 18:00.960
Seriously?
But this could damage my career.

18:01.122 --> 18:03.500
I could be suspended or worse.

18:03.666 --> 18:06.294
Ryan, a call just came
in from Joe's prison.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.844
- Give it to Donovan.
- He wants to talk to you.

18:11.007 --> 18:12.133
Too bad.

18:16.596 --> 18:18.143
Ryan...

18:18.639 --> 18:19.856
...I love you.

18:20.391 --> 18:22.064
But I don't know that I can do this.

18:22.226 --> 18:25.821
I am going to make this right. I promise.

18:42.163 --> 18:44.257
That feels amazing.

18:44.415 --> 18:46.509
Girl, we're just getting started.

18:50.671 --> 18:52.173
Gentler.

18:57.053 --> 18:58.680
Like this.

19:06.354 --> 19:08.027
On, Kyle.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.905
- Name's Walter.
- Heh.

19:12.068 --> 19:13.365
I know.

19:13.527 --> 19:15.450
Do you mind if I call you Kyle?

19:15.655 --> 19:18.033
It's a little game that I like to play.

19:18.199 --> 19:20.418
You can call me whatever you want.

19:23.537 --> 19:27.258
Mm. Mm. Slow down, Kyle.

19:28.167 --> 19:29.259
Kyle.

19:29.919 --> 19:31.546
Slow down.

19:38.386 --> 19:39.603
[YELLS]

20:13.129 --> 20:14.426
- Boo.
- Aah!

20:18.843 --> 20:21.437
Did you really think
you'd get away from me?

21:26.660 --> 21:28.162
[SCREAMS]

21:28.329 --> 21:29.501
Found you.

21:30.372 --> 21:34.172
- Now it's time for you to pay.
- Please, Mark. Mark, don't kill me, please.

21:34.335 --> 21:35.552
No, no. Mark drowned.

21:36.587 --> 21:38.009
I'm Luke.

21:46.013 --> 21:47.060
- There.
- Please, please.

21:47.223 --> 21:49.567
God. Now, you, you betrayed Mark.

21:49.725 --> 21:52.069
He had a soft spot for you,
and you played him.

21:52.228 --> 21:53.696
It wasn't me, it was Strauss.

21:53.854 --> 21:55.356
She said, lying.

21:57.399 --> 22:00.073
He would've killed me
if I didn't do exactly what he said.

22:00.236 --> 22:02.739
Please, we're exactly the same, you and me.

22:02.905 --> 22:04.532
We both lost people we loved.

22:05.032 --> 22:06.579
Please.

22:07.368 --> 22:08.415
Poor thing.

22:08.577 --> 22:10.921
You're just a broken-winged bird,
aren't you?

22:12.456 --> 22:14.458
I'm gonna put you out of your misery.

22:14.667 --> 22:17.216
No, I know how to get to Mike Weston.

22:22.675 --> 22:23.722
Hey, guys.

22:23.884 --> 22:27.479
Ryan, I reversed-traced the number Theo
used to call you. Took me to a burner.

22:27.763 --> 22:30.391
- So no GPS?
- Right, but I installed a streaming alert.

22:30.558 --> 22:32.310
He makes another call, we'll have him.

22:32.476 --> 22:35.104
He's not gonna use that phone again.
He's too smart.

22:35.896 --> 22:37.239
GARY:
Bro, I was ready.

22:37.731 --> 22:41.201
Best shape of my life.
PFT scores off the charts.

22:41.735 --> 22:43.612
So, what happened?

22:43.779 --> 22:45.622
My psych eval went sideways.

22:45.781 --> 22:49.206
Jackass captain bounced me
over hostility issues.

22:49.368 --> 22:50.620
[CHUCKLES]

22:51.203 --> 22:52.250
What's his name?

22:52.413 --> 22:54.086
Robert James Tubbs.

22:54.248 --> 22:56.091
He had it out for me from the start.

22:58.752 --> 23:00.129
I was meant for the 12th.

23:00.296 --> 23:01.764
I bleed ranger.

23:01.922 --> 23:04.596
- Never even had a chance.
- No.

23:06.760 --> 23:09.263
I lost my wife and my apartment...

23:09.430 --> 23:12.775
...any dreams I had left.

23:15.436 --> 23:17.939
You can get it all back, you know.

23:19.440 --> 23:21.317
Your manhood...

23:21.483 --> 23:23.281
...your dignity.

23:23.819 --> 23:25.036
Yeah?

23:26.280 --> 23:27.327
How?

23:51.096 --> 23:52.268
[GRUNTS]

23:53.974 --> 23:58.150
The cameras that we planted are still
active. They link to this web portal.

23:58.312 --> 24:01.361
If the FBI found the laptop,
then they would have taken them down.

24:01.523 --> 24:03.400
So somebody else has it.

24:04.652 --> 24:05.824
I don't buy it.

24:05.986 --> 24:08.660
Feds came in the door
90 seconds after Mark split.

24:08.822 --> 24:12.247
Laptop was on your bed. They have it.
Maybe they haven't looked at it yet.

24:12.409 --> 24:16.755
According to this, the laptop was logged
in to this portal every day since the raid.

24:16.914 --> 24:18.666
Somebody's watching Max.

24:18.832 --> 24:21.676
Somebody we can use to get to Mike.

24:27.174 --> 24:28.596
- Don't.
- Hey, relax.

24:28.801 --> 24:31.520
- Mark.
- I told you, Mark's dead.

24:34.515 --> 24:36.108
I'm Luke.

24:45.401 --> 24:47.369
Take off your clothes.

24:47.695 --> 24:49.242
No.

24:53.826 --> 24:55.544
Pretty please?

25:40.122 --> 25:41.749
Is this enough for you?

25:56.263 --> 25:58.311
Or maybe you want more.

26:16.116 --> 26:17.459
Stop it.

26:19.119 --> 26:21.622
I guess Mark's not dead after all.

26:38.430 --> 26:39.477
[GASPS]

26:42.976 --> 26:44.819
Who the hell are you?

26:46.647 --> 26:48.399
Masks on, right? That was the plan.

26:48.565 --> 26:49.737
You need to face him.

26:50.484 --> 26:53.078
Face the man who took your dignity.

26:56.281 --> 26:58.500
- Heh.
- Yeah, that's right.

26:58.659 --> 27:00.661
Twelfth Mountain recruit, remember?

27:00.828 --> 27:03.331
- You turned me out on a psych rap.
- You sick son of a...

27:03.497 --> 27:04.919
Shut up!

27:05.082 --> 27:06.459
Tell him.

27:06.959 --> 27:08.677
Tell him what he cost you.

27:09.002 --> 27:11.255
I gave up everything to be a ranger.

27:11.463 --> 27:12.680
And you took that from me.

27:12.840 --> 27:15.093
You took everything, maggot.

27:16.885 --> 27:18.762
You'll never get away with this.

27:18.929 --> 27:19.976
[GRUNTS]

27:20.681 --> 27:22.274
Again.

27:26.603 --> 27:29.356
- Now, how did that feel?
- Ah, good.

27:29.982 --> 27:31.029
Really good.

27:31.275 --> 27:33.869
Then you're gonna really like this.

27:40.868 --> 27:42.711
[VOMITING]

27:44.163 --> 27:46.211
I thought we were just supposed
to scare him.

27:46.373 --> 27:48.375
He needed to die.

27:48.542 --> 27:51.216
To free you up for things to come.

27:51.712 --> 27:52.929
What are you talking about?

27:53.088 --> 27:56.513
Do you think I just stumbled across you
by accident?

27:58.177 --> 27:59.895
I sought you out, soldier.

28:00.596 --> 28:03.019
- Why?
- Because you're special.

28:03.390 --> 28:04.733
I am?

28:04.892 --> 28:06.360
Yeah.

28:06.935 --> 28:08.687
In fact...

28:10.230 --> 28:12.028
...you have the potential...

28:12.524 --> 28:15.198
...to change the course of history.

28:18.197 --> 28:20.620
Like that dude from The Matrix.

28:21.325 --> 28:23.043
Exactly.

28:23.202 --> 28:25.705
Man, I can't wait to rub
Linda's face in this.

28:25.871 --> 28:27.544
You can't.

28:27.706 --> 28:30.459
Your ex-wife never
believed in you, I get it.

28:31.376 --> 28:32.548
You are the one, Gary.

28:33.545 --> 28:35.843
And this man's death...

28:36.048 --> 28:38.096
...signifies your rebirth.

28:41.428 --> 28:45.478
Hey, Mike. So, you know the project
you're working on with Sloan?

28:45.641 --> 28:46.984
Tracking down Mark's laptop.

28:47.142 --> 28:50.567
Yeah. Uh, Ryan's got a running point on
Theo's calls, so she asked me to take over.

28:50.854 --> 28:53.824
- What?
- Nothing. I'm just surprised you said yes.

28:53.982 --> 28:56.326
You shouldn't be.
Mark belongs behind bars.

28:56.485 --> 28:59.785
- I'll do what it takes to put him there.
- Even working closely with me?

28:59.947 --> 29:02.871
- Do you wanna see what I found or not?
- Lead the way.

29:18.382 --> 29:19.429
Give me your mask.

29:19.591 --> 29:21.311
There's a river nearby.
We'll dump it there.

29:21.468 --> 29:23.596
Ah, I left it in the house.

29:25.639 --> 29:27.641
- Where?
- In the kitchen.

29:27.808 --> 29:29.606
- I'll go get it.
- No.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.192
I'll get it. You wait here.

29:43.490 --> 29:45.288
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

29:49.621 --> 29:51.498
Linda. Hey, it's...

29:51.665 --> 29:52.962
LINDA:
I warned you not to call.

29:53.125 --> 29:54.843
No, you listen.

29:55.002 --> 29:57.471
You were wrong about me, all right?

29:57.629 --> 29:59.882
I'm not a loser, I'm the one.

30:00.048 --> 30:02.927
And you're gonna be sorry
that you ever let me get away.

30:18.233 --> 30:19.655
- Let's go.
- All right.

30:25.490 --> 30:26.537
RYAN:
Talk to me.

30:26.700 --> 30:28.418
You were right not to go see Joe.

30:28.577 --> 30:31.547
It was just a ploy
to get more face time with you.

30:32.164 --> 30:34.758
- Are you really skipping the execution?
- Yup.

30:34.958 --> 30:38.508
I would think you, of all people,
would wanna watch him die.

30:39.379 --> 30:41.882
I'm tired of watching people die.

30:42.549 --> 30:44.347
Ryan. Theo used the phone again.

30:44.509 --> 30:46.511
Outside a home in Waynesboro, Virginia.

30:49.723 --> 30:52.021
Home belongs to Captain Robert Tubbs,
U.S. Army.

30:52.184 --> 30:53.231
What's his connection?

30:53.393 --> 30:56.067
I don't know,
but it looks like Theo just killed him.

30:56.229 --> 30:59.108
Waynesboro P.D. responded
to a 911 call 30 minutes ago.

30:59.274 --> 31:01.447
Shots fired.

31:01.610 --> 31:03.988
This is how they found Tubbs.

31:04.905 --> 31:08.705
Tear his life apart. There's gotta be some
reason he drove there to kill this guy.

31:08.867 --> 31:11.211
Lucky break,
Theo using that phone again. But why?

31:12.537 --> 31:14.039
What's he doing?

31:14.206 --> 31:15.924
[DOOR BUZZES]

31:26.593 --> 31:27.719
You lost, Gary?

31:27.886 --> 31:32.107
No, no. I just, uh, got reassigned from gen
pop. I guess you guys are Shorthanded, so...

31:32.265 --> 31:34.267
First I'm hearing about it.

31:34.434 --> 31:36.778
Just relax, Gary.
I've taken care of everything.

31:36.937 --> 31:38.484
Just tell him to check the system.

31:38.647 --> 31:40.115
Check the system.

31:53.578 --> 31:55.922
Are you clear
on the heightened security protocols?

31:56.081 --> 31:57.253
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

31:58.333 --> 32:00.006
Be smart.

32:00.168 --> 32:01.590
These guys are carnivores.

32:05.424 --> 32:06.801
[DOOR BUZZES]

32:09.845 --> 32:10.937
I'm in.

32:27.446 --> 32:29.699
Tell Joe Theo says hello.

32:33.326 --> 32:34.828
Theo says hi.

32:48.091 --> 32:51.766
It's been a long time, Joe.

32:52.053 --> 32:53.930
You've become quite the celebrity.

32:54.097 --> 32:56.896
Yeah, I could say the same about you.

32:57.100 --> 33:02.402
Strauss clearly had his best student
under wraps.

33:03.064 --> 33:06.443
I may have been the best
at embracing his philosophy, but...

33:06.610 --> 33:08.738
...you were always special.

33:14.117 --> 33:15.289
Tell me, Theo.

33:15.702 --> 33:20.424
Is this friend of yours
here to break me out?

33:20.582 --> 33:23.961
Because I'm afraid he appears a little...

33:24.127 --> 33:26.971
...underqualified for the job.

33:27.464 --> 33:29.091
No offense.

33:29.257 --> 33:31.476
Sadly, there's nothing
I can do to save you.

33:31.635 --> 33:34.104
So why the social call?

33:34.429 --> 33:37.933
Oh, unless you were hoping I can save you.

33:38.099 --> 33:40.101
Nothing gets past you, Joe.

33:40.268 --> 33:42.111
No wonder you were Strauss' favorite.

33:42.270 --> 33:44.113
Oh, Theo.

33:44.272 --> 33:46.650
Flattery is so pedestrian.

33:48.276 --> 33:51.155
Frankly, I'm insulted
you think I'm so easily manipulated.

33:51.321 --> 33:54.200
- So then let's cut to the chase.
- Mm.

33:54.366 --> 33:56.835
Strauss used a special code
to protect his secrets.

33:56.993 --> 33:58.620
GARY:
The code that can be deciphered...

33:58.787 --> 34:01.165
...using a key phrase
chosen by the creator.

34:01.331 --> 34:02.503
GARY:
It's old-school. it's...

34:02.666 --> 34:05.670
The simplicity makes it almost unbreakable.

34:05.835 --> 34:08.509
But I think Strauss entrusted you
with that key.

34:09.130 --> 34:10.677
Well, why would I help you?

34:12.676 --> 34:14.349
What do I get in return?

34:15.387 --> 34:16.513
Infamy.

34:18.181 --> 34:20.183
You're gonna die, Joe.

34:20.350 --> 34:23.478
If you're smart, your legacy continues
and the murders that follow...

34:23.645 --> 34:25.487
GARY:
...will be yours.

34:25.647 --> 34:29.150
The infamous Joe Carroll,
killing from beyond the grave.

34:29.484 --> 34:31.031
Immortality.

34:33.321 --> 34:35.995
- What do you have?
- I went through the evidence logged...

34:36.157 --> 34:39.831
...from Mark's safe
house, and I found this.

34:40.328 --> 34:42.001
- Receipt.
- For a laptop.

34:42.163 --> 34:45.212
Purchased in Rego Park. I have the BIA.

34:45.375 --> 34:48.549
If someone is using the laptop,
we can find them in real time.

34:48.712 --> 34:51.306
WESTON: How?
- I'll just enter the ID into our system.

34:51.464 --> 34:52.511
See if it pings.

34:52.674 --> 34:54.847
WESTON: If not,
we'll submit warrants to the telecoms.

34:55.010 --> 34:56.353
Maybe we can find it that way.

34:56.511 --> 34:58.229
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

35:05.812 --> 35:07.029
Sorry.

35:11.860 --> 35:13.032
That was fast.

35:13.194 --> 35:15.242
- It's in the building.
- What?

35:19.034 --> 35:20.536
- Where?
- I don't know.

35:20.702 --> 35:23.581
It's reading as passively connected.
Let me isolate the router.

35:23.747 --> 35:25.215
Pinpoint the exact location.

35:52.776 --> 35:55.620
- The signal just disappeared.
- It must have been powered down.

36:05.955 --> 36:07.502
Ryan.

36:08.583 --> 36:12.429
We got a problem. Someone on our team
took a laptop from Mark's safe house.

36:12.754 --> 36:14.756
- We might have another mole.
- What?

36:14.923 --> 36:16.391
I got something.

36:16.925 --> 36:19.303
The number that Theo's phone called
is registered...

36:19.469 --> 36:22.097
...to a Linda Benson in Charlottesville.

36:22.263 --> 36:26.143
Local police rousted her, and she said that
the call came from her ex-husband, Gary.

36:26.309 --> 36:28.812
- What do we know about Gary?
- Hang on.

36:32.607 --> 36:35.201
He's a guard at Joe's prison.

36:38.655 --> 36:43.456
You know, Theo,
I greatly admire your ingenuity.

36:43.618 --> 36:46.497
But you haven't won me over yet.

36:46.788 --> 36:48.882
Gonna need a little...

36:49.040 --> 36:50.292
...incentive.

36:51.626 --> 36:55.130
- What?
- You've had a lot of quality Ryan time.

36:55.296 --> 36:57.173
But he has someone new in his life.

36:57.340 --> 36:58.887
A new love.

36:59.050 --> 37:00.802
Who is she?

37:03.263 --> 37:04.310
Her name's Gwen.

37:04.639 --> 37:06.482
- Beautiful woman.
- Mm?

37:07.183 --> 37:10.153
A doctor, and they're living together.

37:11.438 --> 37:15.159
Yeah, his new life that doesn't include me.

37:15.316 --> 37:17.944
I know how much that hurts you, Joe.

37:18.653 --> 37:22.533
You give me what I want,
I will punish Ryan Hardy for both of us.

37:23.324 --> 37:26.373
Ryan Hardy belongs to me.

37:29.706 --> 37:31.879
You're gonna be dead in 36 hours.

37:32.041 --> 37:34.715
I am offering you an opportunity
to live beyond death.

37:34.878 --> 37:38.553
To strike out at the man who took
everything from you. Yes or no?

37:42.510 --> 37:44.228
MAN [OVER PA]:
Code six, death row. Full...

37:44.387 --> 37:47.061
Looks like your little monkey
has been discovered. Heh.

37:47.223 --> 37:49.191
Theo, they're coming. What do I do?

37:49.350 --> 37:51.023
Oh! Hey, look out!

37:53.772 --> 37:55.365
Yes.

37:56.357 --> 37:57.574
I'm sorry, Theo.

37:57.859 --> 38:00.954
I'm not ready to pass
on the torch just yet.

38:01.112 --> 38:04.082
Not while I still have a card left to play.

38:04.908 --> 38:06.376
[NECK SNAPS]

38:17.295 --> 38:18.797
GUARD:
Man down!

38:19.714 --> 38:21.136
Don't move! Do not move.

38:25.553 --> 38:27.055
Let's go.

38:27.764 --> 38:29.391
Come on, move!

38:36.064 --> 38:37.532
So...

38:38.066 --> 38:39.943
...you know Theo.

38:40.401 --> 38:43.951
I tried to tell you, but you insisted on
sending Agent One-Eye in your place.

38:44.155 --> 38:45.748
What did Theo want from you?

38:45.907 --> 38:46.954
What did you tell him?

38:47.116 --> 38:50.336
You know, I have to say, Ryan,
I'm very disappointed in you.

38:50.662 --> 38:54.383
It almost feels like
you don't wanna be friends anymore.

38:54.541 --> 38:56.543
I'm not your friend.

38:56.709 --> 38:59.758
I am the guy that killed all your
followers, put you on death row.

38:59.921 --> 39:01.923
Now, tell me...

39:02.590 --> 39:05.343
Tell me where the hell he is.

39:05.510 --> 39:06.557
Why?

39:06.719 --> 39:09.768
Why should I?
You're not exactly being very pleasant.

39:09.931 --> 39:11.899
I'll tell you what.

39:12.058 --> 39:13.810
Why don't we have a sleepover?

39:13.977 --> 39:18.232
You know, they built this wing just for me,
so you could bunk up next door...

39:18.398 --> 39:20.400
...and we could chat the night away.

39:22.110 --> 39:23.908
We could chat about Gwen.

39:24.195 --> 39:26.914
I gather she's a looker. And a doctor.

39:28.533 --> 39:30.080
[GRUNTING]

39:32.579 --> 39:35.207
GUARD 1: Let go. Get off.
GUARD 2: Come on, let go!

39:35.665 --> 39:36.962
Back off!

39:38.376 --> 39:39.423
All right, all right.

39:41.671 --> 39:43.218
Oh, such passion.

39:43.590 --> 39:47.015
Just goes to show
how much you really care about me.

39:47.427 --> 39:49.646
And there was I, getting all worried.

39:49.804 --> 39:51.226
I can't do this anymore.

39:52.181 --> 39:54.400
Yeah, of course you can.

39:54.559 --> 39:56.778
All you have to do is accept...

39:56.936 --> 39:59.985
...that I'm the most important relationship
in your life.

40:00.857 --> 40:01.983
No, you're not.

40:03.443 --> 40:04.490
You're diseased.

40:05.278 --> 40:07.622
Tomorrow night, when they kill you...

40:09.949 --> 40:11.246
...I'll be cured.

40:18.291 --> 40:20.339
[SECURITY PANEL BEEPING]

40:55.745 --> 40:57.292
[TOILET FLUSHES]

40:58.206 --> 40:59.378
Gwen?

40:59.540 --> 41:01.508
GWEN: In the bathroom. Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

41:02.168 --> 41:04.637
I just, uh, broke a glass. Don't come out.

41:05.755 --> 41:09.180
GWEN: I thought you'd be home for dinner.
Did something happen?

41:13.513 --> 41:15.060
No...

41:19.102 --> 41:20.149
No, I just, um...

41:20.311 --> 41:22.029
I was just, uh...

41:30.530 --> 41:31.656
I saw Joe.

41:33.741 --> 41:35.835
Theo reached out to him.

41:36.202 --> 41:39.877
I thought going to the prison
was the right thing to do, I was wrong.

41:40.623 --> 41:42.296
- It's okay.
- No.

41:42.458 --> 41:45.007
- Ryan...
- No, it's not.

41:45.169 --> 41:48.969
You are the most important thing
in my life...

41:49.298 --> 41:51.426
...and I keep screwing it up.

41:51.592 --> 41:53.344
I don't wanna lose you, doc.

41:53.594 --> 41:54.686
I'm gonna do better.

41:58.266 --> 41:59.984
I love you.

42:02.353 --> 42:04.572
I love you too. I'll be out in a minute.

42:05.940 --> 42:07.283
RYAN:
Okay.

42:09.444 --> 42:11.162
[SOBBING]

43:51.671 --> 43:53.673
[English - US - SDH]
